amortized over the average remaining service period of U.S. participants, which was approximately 7 years as of 30
September 2019. For U.K. participants, accumulated actuarial gains and losses that exceed a corridor are amortized
over the average remaining life expectancy, which was approximately 25 years as of 30 September 2019.
